{"content": "Given the function:\n\\[\nf(x) = x^7 + a x^3 + c x\n\\]\n\nWe know:\n\\[\nf(5) = 3\n\\]\n\nWe want to find \\( f(-5) \\).\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Evaluate \\( f(5) \\)\n\n\\[\nf(5) = 5^7 + a \\cdot 5^3 + c \\cdot 5 = 5^7 + 125a + 5c\n\\]\nGiven \\( f(5) = 3 \\), so:\n\\[\n5^7 + 125a + 5c = 3\n\\]\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Find \\( f(-5) \\)\n\n\\[\nf(-5) = (-5)^7 + a(-5)^3 + c(-5) = -5^7 - 125a - 5c\n\\]\n\n---\n\n### Step 3: Relate \\( f(-5) \\) to \\( f(5) \\)\n\nAdd the two expressions:\n\\[\nf(5) + f(-5) = (5^7 + 125a + 5c) + (-5^7 - 125a - 5c) = 0\n\\]\n\nTherefore,\n\\[\nf(-5) = -f(5) = -3\n\\]\n\n---\n\n### Final answer:\n\\[\n\\boxed{-3}\n\\]\n\nSo the", "in": 292, "out": 300}